<html><head><meta charset="utf-8" /><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" /><title>10 - Collections</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.5;padding:24px;max-width:900px;margin:auto}header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center}nav a{margin:0 8px}.section{margin:20px 0}.quiz-btn{display:inline-block;padding:10px 14px;background:#0078d4;color:#fff;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none}</style></head><body><header><div><a href="../index.html">◀ Back to course</a></div><div><strong>Java • Topic 10</strong></div></header><h1 id="title">Collections</h1><p class="lead">List, Set, Map, and the Collections Framework basics.</p><div class="section" id="overview"><h2>Overview</h2><p>Choose the right collection based on ordering and duplicates.</p></div><div class="section" id="details"><h2>Details</h2><p>Examples with ArrayList, HashSet, and HashMap.</p></div><div class="section" id="practice"><h2>Try it</h2><p>Write code to count word frequency using a Map.</p></div><div class="section" id="navigation"><nav><a href="09-exceptions">◀ Previous</a><a href="../index.html">Course index</a><a href="11-streams">Next ▶</a></nav></div><div class="section"><a class="quiz-btn" href="#" data-quiz="quiz.json">Take Quiz</a></div></body></html>
